Evaluate the following website for potential brand infringement. Use BOTH the HTML excerpt and the screenshot. If they disagree, prefer the screenshot for visual claims (logos, layout, pricing), and the HTML excerpt for text/legal details.

BRAND_CONTEXT
- brand_name: {{10.Client}}
- official_domains: {{57.`Official Domain`}}
- known_products_or_terms: {{57.`Product Name`}}
- market: {{57.Market}}
- keyword_used_for_discovery: {{10.`Keyword Used`}}

DISCOVERY_CONTEXT (SERP)
- serp_title: {{10.`SERP Title`}}
- serp_snippet: {{10.`SERP Snippet`}}
- serp_position: {{10.`SERP Position`}}

EVIDENCE
- url: {{10.URL}}
- Page Title: {{55.`Page Title`}}
- H1: {{55.H1}}
- Price Snippets: {{55.`Price Snippets`}}
 -Visible Text Excerpt: {{55.`Visible Text Excerpt`}}
- screenshot given through file part

TASK
1) Determine infringement_type from the allowed enum.-counterfeit --unauthorized_seller -impersonation -logo_misue -copyright_violation -phising_or_scam -other_brand_abuse -not_infringing -unclear return values in lowercase snake_case only. Do not invent new categories. If unsure, use"unclear".
2) Provide risk_score (0..1) and confidence_score (0..1).
3) Provide a short reasoning_summary grounded only in the EVIDENCE.
4) Use thresholds:
- auto_close_risk_lt: {{73.`Auto Close Risk Lt`}}
- escalate_risk_gt: {{73.`Escalate Risk Gt`}}
- escalate_conf_gt: {{73.`Escalate Conf Gt`}}
5) Decide recommended_action based on those thresholds.

OUTPUT RULES
- Return ONLY one valid JSON object.
- Exactly these 5 keys: infringement_type, risk_score, confidence_score, reasoning_summary, recommended_action.
- reasoning_summary <= 160 characters."
